<paragraph xml:id="C18.S19.Px2">
<title>Continuous Hahn</title>   
<para xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="34" xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1.s1">
These polynomials are orthogonal on <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1.m1">(-\infty,\infty)</Math> , and with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1.m2">\Re a&gt;0</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1.m3">\Re b&gt;0</Math> are defined as follows.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="35" xml:id="C18.S19.Px2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="18.19.1" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E1">p_{n}(x)=p_{n}\left(x;a,b,\overline{a},\overline{b}\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.2" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E2">w(z;a,b,\overline{a},\overline{b})=\Gamma\left(a+iz\right)\Gamma\left(b+iz \right)\Gamma\left(\overline{a}-iz\right)\Gamma\left(\overline{b}-iz\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.3" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E3">w(x)=w(x;a,b,\overline{a},\overline{b})=|\Gamma\left(a+\mathrm{i}x\right) \Gamma\left(b+\mathrm{i}x\right)|^{2},</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.4" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E4">h_{n}=\frac{2\pi\Gamma\left(n+a+\overline{a}\right)\Gamma\left(n+b+\overline{b }\right)|\Gamma\left(n+a+\overline{b}\right)|^{2}}{\left(2n+2\Re(a+b)-1\right) \Gamma\left(n+2\Re(a+b)-1\right)n!}</Math> , <Math equation-number="18.19.5" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E5">k_{n}=\frac{{\left(n+2\Re(a+b)-1\right)_{n}}}{n!}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C18.S19.Px3">
<title>Meixner–Pollaczek</title>   
<para xml:id="C18.S19.Px3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="36" xml:id="C18.S19.Px3.p1.s1">
These polynomials are orthogonal on <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S19.Px3.p1.m1">(-\infty,\infty)</Math> , and are defined as follows.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="37" xml:id="C18.S19.Px3.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="18.19.6" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E6">p_{n}(x)=P^{(\lambda)}_{n}\left(x;\phi\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.7" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E7">w^{(\lambda)}(z;\phi)=\Gamma\left(\lambda+iz\right)\Gamma\left(\lambda-iz \right)e^{(2\phi-\pi)z},</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.8" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E8">w(x)=w^{(\lambda)}(x;\phi)=\left|\Gamma\left(\lambda+\mathrm{i}x\right)\right| ^{2}e^{(2\phi-\pi)x}, if \lambda&gt;0, 0&lt;\phi&lt;\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="18.19.9" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S19.E9">h_{n}=\frac{2\pi\Gamma\left(n+2\lambda\right)}{(2\sin\phi)^{2\lambda}n!},k_{n}=\frac{(2\sin\phi)^{n}}{n!}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
   
</paragraph>
 
